Intoxication

%c[0,170,170,170]Disruption of the body’s vital activity resulting from ingestion of poison or toxin, as well as the action that caused this disease. The main groups of substances that cause acute poisoning are:

 %c[0,153,255,255] • %c[ui_green]Drugs;

 %c[0,153,255,255] • %c[ui_green]Alcohol and surrogates;

 %c[0,153,255,255] • %c[ui_green]Cauterizing liquids;

 %c[0,153,255,255] • %c[ui_green]Carbon monoxide;

 %c[0,153,255,255] • %c[ui_green]Mushrooms
